# Copy to .env (gitignored, never committed) to configure optional
# remote HTTPS access via Cloudflare Tunnel. Everything works fine
# LAN-only with none of this set.
#
# See docs/remote_access_cloudflare_tunnel.md for full setup steps.

# Note: no API URL configuration is needed. The frontend uses
# same-origin relative paths and nginx proxies /api and /ws to the
# backend, so the same build works on the LAN (offline) and through a
# tunnel. You only need ONE public hostname route in Cloudflare,
# pointing at localhost:8090.

# From Cloudflare Zero Trust dashboard -> Networks -> Tunnels -> your
# tunnel -> "Install and run a connector" step (a long token string).
# Only takes effect when running with: docker compose --profile cloudflare-tunnel up -d
# CLOUDFLARE_TUNNEL_TOKEN=

# Only needed on 32-bit ARM (Raspberry Pi 2/3 on 32-bit Raspberry Pi OS).
# Cloudflare publishes no official armv7 cloudflared image, so an
# unofficial multi-arch build is required there. Leave unset on
# amd64/arm64 to use Cloudflare's own official image.
# CLOUDFLARED_IMAGE=erisamoe/cloudflared:latest

# Camera - USB webcam connected directly to the Pi, streamed natively
# by the backend itself (ffmpeg + MJPEG-over-HTTP, no separate relay
# service). See docs/cctv_camera_setup.md. Always active, no profile
# flag needed - if no webcam is attached, the camera endpoint just
# returns a clear error rather than the whole app failing.
# Defaults to /dev/video0 - override if `ls /dev/video*` on the Pi
# shows your webcam registered at a different path.
# WEBCAM_DEVICE=/dev/video0

# App-wide password gate for sensitive features (camera; future relay
# control). Enter once on a device, remembered from then on (a token
# is stored in that browser's localStorage) - no re-entry needed.
# Leave unset and the gate is a complete no-op - the app works exactly
# as it does today. A single shared password, not per-user accounts -
# matches a one-household van, not a multi-tenant product.
# APP_ACCESS_PASSWORD=

# AI Recommendations ("what's cool nearby right now") - optional. Uses
# Claude (Anthropic API) to suggest genuine local things to see/do near
# your current location. Costs a small amount per call to Anthropic -
# see docs/ai_features.md for real cost figures. Leave unset and this
# feature just shows as "not configured" - nothing else in the app
# depends on it.
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
# Optional override - defaults to Haiku (cheapest, fast, appropriate
# for this task).
# AI_RECOMMENDATIONS_MODEL=claude-haiku-4-5-20251001

# Camera image rotation, for a webcam physically mounted upside down
# or on its side. Valid values: 0, 90, 180, 270. Applied server-side so
# it's correct everywhere the snapshot is consumed, not just in the
# browser. Anything else is ignored with a warning and treated as 0.
# CAMERA_ROTATION=180
